Note: After an unwanted reset (destructive or functional) the latest registers can be read, which is required for failure analysis.
Size: 307 Bytes
Session Control: 0x4F - Development Session
Security Access Level: No Access Protection
Format: <2 Bytes reset counter + 5 entries * 61 Bytes>
Valid values: 0x00000000 .. 0xFFFFFFFF
When a new reset occurs, the crash data will be logged in the circular buffer in the NvM at entry: reset counter MOD 5. Reset counter is incremented by 1.
Bytes 0-1: Reset counter (0x0000 .. 0xFFFF)
Space for 5 entries (at byte offsets: 2, 63, 124, 185, 246) with layout:
Common Fixed Header (Bytes 0-19): Byte 0: Reset_Error_Code (Multiplexor: 1: MachineCheck Exception / OS Exception, 2: Watchdog Reset, 3: SystemIntegrity FCCU Reset, 4: SystemIntegrity Reset due to Register Monitoring, 5: MPU Reset, 255: Unknown Reset) Bytes 1-4: SwVersionNumber (char[4] SW version number from GW2020_VWSoftwareVersionNumber_F189) Byte 5: Year (0..99) Byte 6: Bit 3-0: Month (1..12) Bit 7-4: Day part1(1..31) Byte 7: Bit 1-0: Day part2 (1..31) Bit 7-2: Hour (0..23) Byte 8: Bit 5-0: Minute (0..59) Bit 7-6: CoreId (0: Core0, 1: Core1, 2: Core2) Byte 9: TaskId (8 bit) Bytes 10-11: SubTask + SlotId (8 bit index + 8 bit index) Bytes 12-15: Program Counter (32 bit address) Bytes 16-19: Stack Pointer (32 bit address)
+ Payload containing crash dump context data in the following bytes:
Variable layout data depending of type of reset (Bytes 20-60):
1) Data type: MachineCheck Exception / OS Exception: Byte 20: IVPR Interrupt vector offset (see µC Manual: 0x00: Critical Input Interrupt, 0x10: Machine Check Interrupt, 0x20: Data Storage Interrupt, 0x30: Instruction Storage Interrupt, ...) Bytes 21-24: MCSSR0/DSRR0/CSSR0 (depending on Interrupt vector offset) (32 bit address) Bytes 25-28: MCSSR1/DSRR1/CSSR1 (depending on Interrupt vector offset) (32 bit address) Bytes 29-32: MCSR/DEAR/ESR/DBSR (depending on Interrupt vector offset) (32 bit address) Bytes 33-36: MCAR (32 bit address) Bytes 37-40: FuncCall1 (32 bit address) Bytes 41-44: FuncCall2 (32 bit address) Bytes 45-48: FuncCall3 (32 bit address) Bytes 49-52: FuncCall4 (32 bit address) Bytes 53-56: FuncCall5 (32 bit address) Bytes 57-60: FuncCall6 (32 bit address)
2) Data type: Watchdog Reset: Bytes 20-23: RGM_DES (32 bit address) Bytes 24-27: RGM_FES (32 bit address) Bytes 28-31: Program Counter Core0 (WdgM) (32 bit address) Bytes 32-35: Stack Pointer Core0 (WdgM) (32 bit address) Bytes 36-39: Program Counter Core2 (WdgM) (32 bit address) Bytes 40-43: Stack Pointer Core2 (WdgM) (32 bit address) Bytes 44-45: SubTask + SlotId C0 (8 bit index + 8 bit index) Bytes 46-47: SubTask + SlotId C1 (8 bit index + 8 bit index) Byte 48: task_id_c0 (8 bit Id) Byte 49: task_id_c1 (8 bit Id) Bytes 50-60: Reserved Note: information in watchdog reset reason may be redundant. slotId is 32bit, but only 8 bit are relevant.
3) Data type: SystemIntegrity FCCU Reset: Bytes 20-23: RGM_DES (32 bit address) Bytes 24-27: RGM_FES (32 bit address) Byte 28: FCCU fault channel (8 bit channel index) (0: no error, 1 - 128: channel (0..127) index+1 , 255: multiple error) Bytes 29-32: FCCU Status RF_S0 (32 bit) Bytes 33-36: FCCU Status RF_S1 (32 bit) Bytes 37-40: FCCU Status RF_S2 (32 bit) Bytes 41-44: FCCU Status RF_S3 (32 bit) Byte 45: FCCU Last State (0: Normal, 1: Fault, 2: Alarm to Fault) Byte 46: ECC ErrType (0: RAM ECC, 1: ROM ECC) Bytes 47-50: ECC Error Address (32 bit address) Bytes 51-60: Reserved
4) Data type: SystemIntegrity Reset due to Register Monitoring: Bytes 20-23: RGM_DES (32 bit address) Bytes 24-27: RGM_FES (32 bit address) Byte 28: Register Monitoring Error Code ( 0 : No Error, 1: SAR_ADC_MCR, 2: SAR_ADC_ICNCMR0, 3: SAR_ADC_ICNCMR1, 4: SAR_ADC_ICNCMR2, 5:SAR_ADC_CTR0, 6: SAR_ADC_CTR1, 7: SAR_ADC_CTR2, 8: SAR_ADC_CTR3, 9: XBIC_0_MCR, 10: XBIC_1_MCR, 11: SMPU_0_CESR0, 12: SMPU_1_CESR0, 13: E2ECTL0, 14: DMEMCTL1, 15: L1CSR1, 255: WRONG_CORE_CONTEXT) Bytes 29-32: Register Value On Error (32 bit register) Bytes 33-60: Reserved
5) Data type: MPU Reset: Bytes 20-23: RGM_DES (32 bit address) Bytes 24-27: RGM_FES (32 bit address) Bytes 28-31: CESR0 (32 bit register) Bytes 32-35: CESR1 (32 bit register) Bytes 36-39: EARx( EARx != 0, bus_id = x) (32 bit register) Bytes 40-43: EDRx( EDRx != 0, bus_id = x) (32 bit register) Byte 44: Bus_Id (8 bit Id) Bytes 45-48: MPU0CSR0 (32 bit register) Bytes 49-60: Reserved
